<chapter xml:id='chap-filter'
         xmlns='http://docbook.org/ns/docbook' version='5.0' xml:lang='en'
         xmlns:xsi='http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance'
         xsi:schemaLocation='http://docbook.org/ns/docbook
                     http://docbook.org/xml/5.0/xsd/docbook.xsd'
         xmlns:xlink='http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink'
         xmlns:xinclude='http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude'>
 <title>Maven Filtering</title>

 <para>
  Maven filtering works in XML, text files, and JSON
  according to the fix for
  <link
   xlink:show="new"
   xlink:href="https://bugster.forgerock.org/jira/browse/DOCS-178"
  >DOCS-178</link>.
 </para>

 <para>
  The following is a filtered JSON file.
 </para>

 <programlisting language="javascript">
<xinclude:include href="../shared/DOCS-178.json" parse="text">
 <xinclude:fallback>
  Failed to include file.
 </xinclude:fallback>
</xinclude:include>
 </programlisting>

 <para>
  The following is a filtered text file.
 </para>

 <programlisting language="none">
<xinclude:include href="../shared/DOCS-178.txt" parse="text">
 <xinclude:fallback>
  Failed to include file.
 </xinclude:fallback>
</xinclude:include>
 </programlisting>

 <para>
  The following is filtered directly in this file.
 </para>

 <programlisting language="xml">
<![CDATA[
<project>
 <projectName>${projectName}</projectName>
 <projectVersion>${project.version}</projectVersion>
</project>
]]>
 </programlisting>

 <para>
  The following is an example that was failing in OpenIDM docs:
 </para>

 <screen>$ unzip openicf-zip-${openicf.remoteconnectorserver.version}.zip</screen>
</chapter>
